name: NPR
text:
Phil Niekro, the National Baseball Hall of Famer and longtime pitcher for the Braves, has died at age 81.

From full-season debut in 1967 until his retirement in 1987, Niekro pitched 5,404 innings — the most by any pitcher in the modern era.
